Commentary Text: Tahir to A Russell, no run, oh dear, Bhajji makes a mess of this skier. Stunned faces in the crowd, they can't believe it. Uff! This is a costly miss, can't give a lifeline to someone like Russell. What have you done Bhajji? Phew. Slower and tempted Russell, who clears his front leg and aims a biggie across the line, totally miscue and sends it into the night sky. Bhajji at mid-wicket steadies himself, it was swirling in the air for a long time and he makes a meal of it. So much so that he doesn't even get a hand on it as it lobs behind him. He sort of lost his balance and slipped over

Commentary Text: Tahir to Shubman Gill, out Stumped!! Oh goodness! Has he got another one? Has MSD pulled off a stumping here? Tahir is already celebrating and yes, Gill has started to walk. KKR in complete disarry now with six down. It was the googly from Tahir, such deception that Gill is foxed by the spin. Goes searching for the drive away from his body and doesn't read it at all. It beats his inside edge and overbalances himself by dragging his back leg out of his crease. MSD was quick to spot it and whips the bails off in a flash. No need to go upstairs as well. CSK all over KKR like a rash. Shubman Gill st Dhoni b Tahir 9(12)

Commentary Text: Tahir to Karthik, out Caught by Harbhajan!! Redemption for Tahir. Sombre faces among KKR fans in the stands and Tahir unleashes the Baby-in-the-arms celebration for a change. No celebratory run on this occasion. But poor shot this from Karthik. Just runs out of patience and goes hard on the whippy flick, hits it airly and finds Bhajji at short mid-wicket, who takes a sharp catch. Tahir gave more flight and it kind of dipped which tempted the KKR captain into playing that false shot. Karthik c Harbhajan b Tahir 19(21) [4s-3]

Commentary Text: Chahar to Uthappa, out Caught by Kedar Jadhav!! Outrageous shot from Uthappa! Was looking in good touch but just when he should have started to kick on, falls to a terrible stroke. Despite a deep mid-wicket in place, he goes for the aerial pull off the shortish length ball that had no pace at all. Gets it off the top half of the blade and it's a rather easy catch for Jadhav stationed there, precisely for this kind of a stroke. It's one-way traffic in Chepauk at the moment. KKR don't seem to have turned up yet. Uthappa c Kedar Jadhav b Chahar 11(9) [4s-2]

Commentary Text: Harbhajan to Narine, out Caught by Chahar!! Harbhajan has the last laugh! He is just too good on such surfaces and you can't just slog him away, which is what Narine does to spinners anyway. Used his feet early and made room but Harbhajan cleverly dragged the length back with no pace whatsoever. The result is a miscue that bobbles over the backward point region and Chahar trekked back to take a good tumbling catch. Both the openers sent back to the hut really early. Narine c Chahar b Harbhajan 6(5)

Commentary Text: Narine to Raina, out Caught by Chawla!! In the air and taken. Brilliant catch by PC, he charged back from mid-on, kept his eye on the ball and takes a beauty.
